UML:Class.name: List of Elements in Package Supplements

UML:TaggedValue.value: ➢ Start with selecting User Needs from the "FRAME Repository"
➢ Start with building the Functional View using the Insert Related Elements function on the User Needs or by selecting the Low Level Functions, Data Stores or Terminators from the "FRAME Repository"
➢ Start with building the Organizational View by creating "Actors" and "Organizations" from the FRAME Toolbox
➢ Start with building the Physical View by creating "Components" from the FRAME Toolbox

<memo>#NOTES#<modelview><source customSQL="SELECT t_object.ea_guid AS CLASSGUID, t_object.Object_Type AS CLASSTYPE, t_object.Name, t_object.Object_Type AS [Type], t_object.Status FROM t_object INNER JOIN t_package ON t_package.Package_ID = t_object.Package_ID WHERE t_package.ea_guid = '{76D1A2D4-1A7D-44dc-9705-2E5EB563664A}' ORDER BY t_object.Object_Type, t_object.Name"/></modelview>
